The high T1 General psychopathology and very low self-efficacy suggest initial vulnerability. However, there are significant improvements in self-efficacy and reduction in general psychopathology.

Given the very large increase in Fear of bodily sensations and the initial vulnerability (very low self-efficacy and high psychopathology), I'm inclined to believe this person does develop a psychological disorder between T1 and T2, despite improvements in some areas.

I'll answer "YES" - this person likely develops a psychological disorder between time points T1 and T2.
